<HEADLINE> One Kenyan Killed by Crocodile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- A man was attacked and killed by
a crocodile emerging from a lake in Kenya's Coast Province.
</P>
<P>
The 47-year-old farmer, identified as Samuel Ogundo, fell prey
to the crocodile Tuesday when fishing. He cried for help but the
attack happened too fast and people nearby could not come to his
rescue.
</P>
<P>
The crocodile pulled the body to a deeper part of the lake and
rescuers had to use a canoe to retrieve it, East African Standard
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Local police confirmed the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
