<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Urges Pakistan, India to Restrain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The European Union urged on
Thursday Pakistan and India to restrain from further incidents of
airborne conflicts.
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation bloc described the already tense relations
between the two Asian countries as having "a great impact to the
regional peace and stability".
</P>
<P>
"Incidents during the last 48 hours have caused an increase of
tension in their relations," said a statement issued here.
</P>
<P>
In a second incident in two days of airborne conflict along the
border of Pakistan and India on Wednesday, Pakistan fired at some
Indian military jets and helicopters flying over the crash site of
a Pakistani naval reconnaisance plane that was shot down by India
a day earlier, killing all 16 people on board.
</P>
<P>
The union called for Pakistan and India to show utmost
restraint and responsibility in reacting to these incidents.
</P>
<P>
The union urged the two countries to resume talks as soon as
possible and resolve their differences in a peaceful manner in the
spirit of the Lahore declaration.
</P>
<P>
Though no one was killed or injured in Wednesday's incident,
analysts here feared that the incidents would further strain the
relations between the two countries and led them into another
round of arms race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
