<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0021 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Value-Added Tax to Facilitate Rwanda's Tax Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Value-Added Tax (VAT), due to
replace sales tax by the year 2000, is set to facilitate Rwanda`s
tax reform policy within the next millennium, the Rwanda Revenue
Authority (RRA) said in Kigali Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Henry Kanyesiime Gaperi, deputy-coordinator of VAT at the RRA,
explained that sales tax is the tax levied on the supply of goods
and services. VAT is also levied on the importation of services in
certain circumstances.
</P>
<P>
The Rwanda News Agency quoted Gaperi as saying that the merits
of operating a VAT system far outweigh the demerits.
</P>
<P>
The tax reform policy will be facilitated by introducing VAT
coupled with the abolition of sales tax and the adjustment of
other taxes such as excise tax.
</P>
<P>
"The major ones, however, are the need for increased and
reliable tax revenues to enable the government to perform its
duties honorably, to boost economic growth, competitiveness and
the government's determination to have a fairer tax system," said
Appolinaire Murangira, tax commissioner at the RRA.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the VAT system eliminates cascading through the
credit mechanism to the relief of both traders and consumers,
promotes exports since it zero-rates the exports.
</P>
<P>
Under the same system, there is an automatic credit, Murangira
explained.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that VAT may be inflationary, complicated to
compute and also reduces demand for certain commodities.
</P>
<P>
The business people who have grown jittery about its
implementation said that it is difficult to administer VAT as
keeping records is not simple and is regressive.
</P>
<P>
The government of Rwanda in partnership with other
stake-holders including those in the media industry, will in the
next few months take appropriate measures to ensure that
sensitization about the introduction of VAT in the year 2000 is
carried out smoothly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
