Angop, during the three-day visit, Joao Lourenco and his group
will meet with South African political organizations.
</P>
<P>
Angop also said that the MPLA and the African National Congress
of South Africa (ANC), the country's ruling party, have been
maintaining working relations and friendship, which was
established during the anti-apartheid fight.
</P>
<P>
Analyst said that Lourenco's visit aims to remedy the spoilt
relationship between the two countries, which deteriorated during
the civil war in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) and a
recent accusation against South Africa by the Angolan defense
minister.
</P>
<P>
The two countries held different points of view on the issue of
the civil war in Congo. Angola supported the Southern African
Development Community (SADC) military intervention while South
Africa advocated peaceful negotiations.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Defense Minister Kundy Payama in late July accused
South Africa of measuring forces with Angola in fighting for
regional leadership.
</P>
<P>
Lourenco's delegation will return to Angola Saturday. 
</P>
