<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Agriculture Grows 6.76 Pct in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The agriculture sector of the
Philippines posted a robust 6.76 percent growth in the first half
of the year, Agriculture Secretary Edgardo Angara said Thursday in
a report.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, gross earnings of the agricultural
products in the first semester stood at 286.4 billion pesos (7.16
billion U.S. dollars), 16.03 percent higher than the same period
of 1998.
</P>
<P>
The report said the crops subsector increased by 12.53 percent
in output and it was nearing its 1997 level.
</P>
<P>
In the second place was the livestock subsector with an
increase rate of 5.86 percent. All the subsector's components
outdid their previous year's production performance.
</P>
<P>
The fishery subsector managed to expand by 1.18 percent buoyed
up by the noticeable output gains in commercial and municipal
fishing.
</P>
<P>
However, the poultry subsector failed to sustain its 1998
record as aggregate output dropped by 2.85 percent, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
On the average, prices received by farmers moved up by 8.96
percent from the 1998 levels. The biggest average price increase
of 11.14 percent was noted in the crops subsector, followed by
poultry subsector's 3.39 percent and livestock subsector's 2.60
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
