<HEADLINE> The Truth Has Come Out: People's Daily </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The People's Daily, China's
leading newspaper, will carry a commentary tomorrow, titled "the
Truth Has Come Out," along with a full examination of Falun Gong
leader Li Hongzhi's role in the April 25 illegal gathering at
Zhongnanhai, in a further expose of the outlawed sect.
</P>
<P>
Evidence shows that the illegal gathering was a well-prepared
and well-organized major political incident aimed at exerting
pressure on the Communist Party of China and the central
government, and disrupting the country's stable political
situation, the commentator says.
</P>
<P>
From this incident, people can get a further glimpse of the
true face of Li and the sect's ulterior political motives. His
sophistry and denials will be to no avail, it says.
</P>
<P>
Li has said that he knew nothing about the gathering, but there
is evidence that he was its mastermind, organizer and director,
the commentary points out.
</P>
<P>
Li has also said that he is not interested in politics. But the
fact is that he often agitated practitioners to put pressure on
the government and the media.
</P>
<P>
Li once declared that Falun Gong had no organization. But facts
show that it has a strict organizational system, according to the
commentary.
</P>
<P>
His fallacies reveal the sect's true nature of being anti-
science, anti-human, anti-society, and anti-government, the
commentary says. It concludes that continuous efforts are needed
to carry the struggle against the illegal Falun Gong cult through
to the end. 
</P>
</TEXT>
