<HEADLINE> Greek Equity Prices Soar to New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Greek equity prices surged to new
records Thursday with the general index on the Athens Stock
Exchange (ASE) ending 2.30 percent higher at 4,696.91 points, its
37th record since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also jumped 2.38 percent to 2,635.15
points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 240.3 billion drachmas (about 798 million U.S.
dollars), and advancers led decliners by 146 to 138 with another
10 issues unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The banks and industrials sectors led the increasing stock
market with ending 2.62 percent and 2.93 percent higher
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
