<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Continue To Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- European stocks posted steep
gains for the second straight day Thursday, as investors flocked
into markets amid subsiding fears over the outlook for higher U.S.
interest rates.
</P>
<P>
London's benchmark FTSE 100 swept to a 2.31 percent higher
close at 6,142.5, a gain of 138.9 points, propelled by an early
charge on the Dow Jones industrials.
</P>
<P>
Together with Wednesday's 36-point gain, the FTSE blue chips
have wiped out their 148-point loss from Tuesday's sessions.
</P>
<P>
The new optimism made telecoms look more attractive to UK
investors and the sector rose by 3.5 percent. Telewest
Communications added 16p, or 7.1 percent, to 240.25p.
</P>
<P>
Banks also did well, rising 3 percent. Royal Bank of Scotland
shares closed up 48p at 1,199p. HSBC gained 31p to 746.5, Halifax
jumped 14p to 662p, Barclays put on 50p to 1,779p and Lloyds TSB
was up 12p at 852.5p.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the electronic Xetra Dax jumped 2.15 percent, or
107.74 points, to 5,127.43, supported by a vigorous rally in index
heavyweight Deutsche Telekom.
</P>
<P>
Paris's blue chip CAC 40 advanced 2.27 percent to 4,365.66,
though many traders kept to the sidelines ahead of the Fed's
policy-making meeting on August 24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
