<HEADLINE> Kenya Reopens its Border with Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Kenya has reopened its border
with Somalia because calm has returned on the other side of the
border, a local source said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The border closed early July on the heels of an incident where
a band of Somali militiamen attacked a Kenya army platoon in the
border area in North Eastern Province and snatched two army
lorries, firearms and radio equipment, which were later returned
to the Kenya army.
</P>
<P>
North Eastern Provincial Commissioner Maurice Makhanu said in
his office Thursday that vehicles and nationals of the two
countries were now free to cross the border.
</P>
<P>
However, military personnel at the border would remain to
conduct security surveillance as the U.N. High Commissioner for
Refugees was allowed to ferry refugees at the border to the three
camps in the province, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, police in Garissa District in the province Thursday
gunned down a bandit at the Iffo Refugee Camp and recovered an
AK-47 assault rifle,
</P>
<P>
a bayonet and several round of ammunition.
</P>
<P>
Garissa District Commissioner Salim Ali Mola confirmed the
incident, saying the bandit was in a group which earlier killed a
World Food Program lorry turn boy they had attacked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
