<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stock End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Thursday with the Dow Jones industrial average rising.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed up 1.59 at 10,789.39. The blue chip index rose
as much as 113 points in the trading.
</P>
<P>
But Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 3.77 at 1,298.16 and the
technology heavy Nasdaq index fell 15.49 at 2,549.49.
</P>
<P>
The Treasury's auction of 10 billion U.S. dollars in 30-year
bonds cut almost all the Dow's gain and pushed S&AMP;T and Nasdaq
lower. The move drove the bond's yield up to 6.27 percent and with
yield above 6 percent, bonds are presenting an attractive
alternative to stock investment.
</P>
<P>
The worries about higher interest rates prevailed and had an
effect on the market as the Commerce Department reported a 0.7
percent rise in retail sales in July. The Federal Reserve could
see the increase as an inflationary pressure in the U.S. economy
and therefore raise interest rates to preempt inflation.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index rose 0.41 to 610.63 and the American
Stock Exchange index rose 3.28 at 780.65. The Russell 2000 index
of smaller companies rose 0.63 at 428.82.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues barely outnumbered advancers on the New York
Stock Exchange, with 1,537 down, 1,510 up and 510 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 742.40 million shares from 782.79
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
