<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Swimmers Win Two Golds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, Croatia, August 12 (Xinhua) -- China's Shan Ying won
the women's 100 meters freestyle while the Chinese team won the
relay event as the swimming competition began on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Shan and compatriot Le Ying made a one-two finish for China
when they clocked 55.22 and 57.67 seconds respectively.
</P>
<P>
Croatia's Smiljana Marinovic came third in 58.71 seconds.
</P>
<P>
"I am very satisfied with my results today," said Shan, the
bronze medalist at the 1998 world championships in Perth,
Australia.
</P>
<P>
She added that the time was the best in two years for a Chinese
swimmer since the National Games in 1997.
</P>
<P>
In the 4X100 meters freestyle relay, Shan, Le, Fu Qili and Cui
Li combined to time three minutes, 51.65 seconds, 1.18 seconds
ahead of the Russians. Belarus was third in 4:00.64.
</P>
<P>
European championships runner-up Lorenzo Vismara of Italy won
the men's 50 meters freestyle race.
</P>
<P>
Vismara, who at Istanbul, Turkey, had finished behind Dutch
winner Pieter Van den Hoogenband but ahead of world champion
Alexander Popov,clocked 22.06 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Segei Ashikhmin was second on Thursday in 22.73 and
his compatriot Aleksei Pavlov third in 23.06.
</P>
<P>
World championships silver medalist Jean-Christoph Sarnin took
the men's 100 meters breaststroke in 1:01.72, followed by China's
Zhu Yi in 1:02.26. Russia's Roman Ivanovski was third in 1:03.03.
</P>
<P>
In men's 100 meters butterfly, European runner-up Milos
Milosevic of Croatia grabbed gold in 53.35 seconds, 0.53 seconds
ahead of Russian Vladislav Kulikov.
</P>
<P>
Another Russian Anatolly Poliakov finished third in 53.97.
</P>
<P>
The host country also took the 200 meters individual medley as
the winner Gordan Kozulj clocked 2:03.21. Ukraine's Serhiy
Serhyeyev was second and Lionel Moreau of France third.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Emiliano Brembilla swam the 400 meters freestyle in 3:
50.92 to snatch a gold. Romania's Dragons Coman won the silver
while Eugeniy Bezruchenko the bronze.
</P>
<P>
The women's 50 meters backstroke title went to Slovenia's Metka
Sparavec. Russia's Elena Nazemnova was second and Hanna Kapachenia
of Belarus third. 
</P>
</TEXT>
