<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion in Philippine Govt Agency Kills 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A powerful bomb blast ripped
through a building of a Philippine government agency in Manila at
dawn Friday, killing eight people and injuring 12, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion destroyed the building at the government's main
criminal investigation agency in Manila.
</P>
<P>
But the officials said that they did not know how many people
were inside the building when the bomb went off.
</P>
<P>
At least seven bodies were recovered, and 12 people were
injured, they said. 
</P>
