<HEADLINE> World Champion Sautin Beaten at Military World Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 12 (Xinhua) -- World championships double gold
medalist Dmitry Sautin of Russia was beaten to second by China's
Peng Bo at the Military World Games here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Sautin, also defending champion at the Military World Games,
scored only 633.12 points in three meters springboard, nearly 20
points below Peng.
</P>
<P>
"I was really lucky today," said Peng. "Maybe Sautin was not
accustomed to the colder temperature here. Or he may be too
relaxed as China's top divers did not compete here."
</P>
<P>
Peng said he did not perform well in his last dive and thought
the gold could be gone. But Sautin also failed in his dive to let
Peng win.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to China's Liu Junhong, who collected 632.
04 points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Liu Hengning said Peng was a good all-round diver
which can compete in all three events and had promising prospect.
</P>
</TEXT>
