<HEADLINE> Myong Breaks World Record for Grenade Throwing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Myong Gum Sun from the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea on Thursday broke the world record for
grenade throwing during the women's military pentathlon
competition at the Military World Games here.
</P>
<P>
Myong scored 1078.0 points to improve the previous record held
by China's Wang Lianying, who also competed here and was third on
the overall standings for military pentathlon after four events.
</P>
<P>
Myong now led the overall standings, followed by compatriot Nam
Hui Sun.
</P>
<P>
The last event, cross-country running, will be held on Friday.
</P>
