<P>
In the 4X100 meters freestyle relay, Shan, Le, Fu Qili and Cui
Li combined to time three minutes, 51.65 seconds, 1.18 seconds
ahead of the Russians. Belarus was third in 4:00.64.
</P>
<P>
In another pool, world championships double gold medalist
Dmitry Sautin of Russia was beaten to second by China's Peng Bo in
the men's three meters board.
</P>
<P>
Sautin, also defending champion at the Military World Games,
scored only 633.12 points, nearly 20 points below Peng.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to China's Liu Junhong, who collected 632.
04 points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese women shooters took the individual and team titles in
sports rifle three positions.
</P>
<P>
Shan Hong, World Cup champion in Milan, Italy this year, scored
585 points for the gold, one point better than second placer
Loubov Galkina of Russia. Another Chinese Xu Yimin took home the
bronze with 578 points.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which won the world championship last year,
also took the team gold.
</P>
<P>
China dominated the women's taekwondo competition on Thursday,
winning all the golds.
</P>
<P>
Kong Fantao carried home the under-47kg category gold while
Chen Zhong won in under-72kg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
