<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 8 Killed, 12 Injured in Manila Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A powerful explosion ripped
through a Philippine National Bureau of Investigation building in
Manila early Friday, killing eight people and injuring 12,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
The explosion, which occurred at dawn Friday, shattered windows
up to the third floor of the five-story building, and at least
eight people were killed and 12 injured, officials at the
government agency said.
</P>
<P>
But the officials said they did not know how many people were
inside the building when the incident occurred.
</P>
<P>
"There was a big explosion, and then a fire," said an official
on duty.
</P>
<P>
Fire-fighters extinguished the fire in two hours and bomb
disposal experts then checked for more explosives inside the
building, which houses the National Bureau of Investigation's
special division.
</P>
<P>
At least seven bodies were recovered, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
An investigation into the incident is under way, they said.
</P>
