<HEADLINE> Davenport Beats Huber in Acura Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Lindsay Davenport
beat Germany's Anke Huber 6-2, 6-2 on Thursday in the American
star's first match in the Acura Classic tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
Davenport needed just 58 minutes to dispatch the German, who
pushed Davenport to the limit before losing 7-5, 7-5 last week in
the quarter-finals in Carlsbad, California.
</P>
<P>
No. 7 Barbara Schett of Austria lost the first set 6-2 and was
leading 4-2 with a break point against her in the second when
Natasha Zvereva of Belarus retired because of a twisted ankle.
</P>
<P>
Also in the second round, Conchita Martinez of Spain defeated
Corina Morariu of the United States 7-5, 6-2. Morariu, 21, is best
known as Davenport's doubles partner.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Davenport had a first-round bye and asked
tournament officials for a Thursday start, giving her three days
rest after playing singles and doubles last week in Carlsbad. She
lost in the singles semi-finals to Venus Williams, but won the
doubles, which kept her playing until Sunday. 
</P>
