<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances in Mason Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- American Pete Sampras scored
a 7-5, 7-6 (7-2) victory over Germany's Rainer Schuttler in the
third round of the ATP Championship in Mason, Ohio on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The victory extended Sampras' streak to 19 matches, during
which he has won three tournaments. But as a measure of the way
Sampras has dominated men's tennis - finishing No. 1 a record six
straight years - the 19 victories only tied the third-best streak
of Sampras' career.
</P>
<P>
Schuttler, 49th in ATP Tour rankings, said playing his first
match against Sampras was good experience.
</P>
<P>
Advancing to the quarter-finals with Sampras were defending
champion Patrick Rafter of Australia, who beat 15th-seeded Nicolas
Lapentti of Ecuador 6-2, 6-3; fourth-seeded Yevgeny Kafelnikov of
Russia, who edged Chris Woodruff of the United States 6-4, 6-4;
fifth-seeded Tim Henman of Britain, who ousted 12th-seeded Nicolas
Kiefer of Germany, 6-4, 6-1; and sixth-seeded Gustavo Kuerten of
Brazil, who eliminated 11th-seeded Tommy Haas of Germany 7-5, 7-5.
</P>
