<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 11 Die in Argentina Bus Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 12 (Xinhua) -- About 11 persons died and
six injured when the bus they traveled in caught fire Thursday in
Argentina's southern province of Rosario, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
An intensive police search was launched immediately for the
suspected perpetrator who got on the vehicle with a package which
generated the fire in toilet.
</P>
<P>
The fire quickly spread through the bus, burning to death three
youngsters and eight adults.
</P>
<P>
The injured were rushed to local hospitals for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The rest 31 passengers managed to save their lives by throwing
themselves out of bus windows. 
</P>
</TEXT>
