<HEADLINE> Taiwan Increases Investment in Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua) -- More and more Taiwanese
businesses are investing in this capital of Fujian Province,
facing the island province across the Taiwan Straits, hoping to
use it as a springboard to seek business opportunities in other
parts of the mainland.
</P>
<P>
An official with the Fuzhou Economic and Technical Development
Zone said that by the end of 1998, the zone had introduced 1.1
billion US dollars from Taiwan for 161 projects, accounting for 13
percent of the total Taiwan investment in Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The focus of the investment has changed from the initial labor-
intensive sector to the current technology- and capital-intensive
sectors, with many conglomerates as the investors.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the Taiwan-funded enterprises in the zone realized an
industrial output valued at 10 billion yuan, with the export
volume reaching nearly 300 million US dollars, accounting for 53
percent of the total export volume by overseas-funded enterprises
in the zone.
</P>
<P>
He said that a pilot zone will be set up within the development
zone to further expand economic and trade cooperation across the
straits.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment in 1985, the development zone has
signed contracts on projects involving more than 1.5 billion U.S.
dollars of investment from overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
