<HEADLINE> Qinghai and Tibet Jointly Promote Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The tourism bureau of China's
Tibet Autonomous Region has established an office in Xining, the
capital of Qinghai Province to promote tourism on the Qinghai-
Tibet Plateau, in central and western part of China.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an opening ceremony, the director general of the
Qinghai Tourism Bureau Zhao Yanqi and his Tibetan counterpart Li
Hongfu said that the office marks the beginning of a new era in
tourism cooperation and they say they will coordinate things
better and increase promotions to jointly develop tourism.
</P>
<P>
The two areas have similar geographical conditions, religious
beliefs, and folk customs and have great potential for tourism.
The Qinghai-Tibet Plateau is known as "the roof of the world" and
attracts thousands of tourists and explorers from all over the
world every year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, an air route linking Lhasa, Tibet's capital,
and Xining opened, bringing more tourists to the area. And, now
that the Qinghai-Tibet Highway has been improved, even more
tourists are expected to come this way to Tibet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
