<HEADLINE> China's Trade Increase Benefits Panama Canal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 12 (Xinhua) -- The increase of China's
foreign trade benefits Panama Canal and Colon Free Zone (CFZ), ex-
negotiator of the Torrijos-Carter Treaties Julio Yao said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Yao said that trade expansion between Panama and China,
including Hong Kong, contributes to the development of the free
zone and the interoceanic canal, which depends on the volume of
foreign trade of Latin America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
Yao noted that Panama possesses a strategic importance, which
should not be underrated for the increase of trade between Latin
America and China.
</P>
<P>
This promising panorama must be regarded as an important factor
for CFZ's growth, and it will be of benefit to Panama as well,
said the expert who also holds a chair in international law in the
University of Panama.
</P>
<P>
According to a report published recently by Panama Canal
Authority (PCA), Cosco, one of China's largest shipping firms,
occupies first place in regard to ship transit through the
interoceanic waterway.
</P>
<P>
Yao said the importance of Panama Canal in the coming century
will further grow due to the world trade expansion promoted by
globalization.
</P>
<P>
"That's why it's important for our policies to head toward a
maintenance and development of best relations with the main users
of this interoceanic pathway, among which is China," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
