<HEADLINE> Central Chinese City Reinforces Flood-Control Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese city of Yueyang in
Hunan Province will spend 140 million yuan on further improvements
in its flood-control capability on the Yangtze River which runs
through the city.
</P>
<P>
Every summer, the city has a tough time dealing with the flood
threats so it began a three-year project last year to improve
flood prevention and controls on the river. It has by now set up
20 flood-diversion zones that can handle 9 billion cubic meters of
floodwaters in all.
</P>
<P>
Since last summer, the city has made a considerable effort at
repairing its 163 km. of dikes and has finished rebuilding a 30-km
section. 
</P>
</TEXT>
