<HEADLINE> Chinese, Tajikistan Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said today that there is no barrier to developing good-neighborly
Sino-Tajikistan relations, and it is imperative for the two sides
to promote cooperation in all fields.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks in his talks with Tajikistan President
Emomali Rakhmonov in this northeast China coastal city.
</P>
<P>
He said that bilateral friendly and cooperative ties have been
developing smoothly in recent years, adding that during this
summit, both sides signed a pact on some border issues following
consultations, which was a major event in bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
With regard to those border issues on which the two sides have
not yet reached agreement, Jiang said that they can seek an
acceptable solution through negotiations on the basis of the
border pact reached, in accordance with the acknowledged norms of
international laws, and in the spirit of equal consultation and
mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that China hopes to expand its economic and trade
cooperation with Tajikistan, and that the two sides should find
ways to let their enterprises have a better understanding of each
other and establish direct links, for which the two governments
can provide support.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also praised the progress made in Tajikistan's national
reconciliation process, and President Rakhmonov's efforts and
contributions in this regard.
</P>
<P>
He said that the maintenance of peace and stability in
Tajikistan is conducive to its economic development and the happy
life of its people, and will also be of significance for peace and
stability in Central Asia.
</P>
</TEXT>
