<HEADLINE> Chinese, Tajikistan Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Briefing Rakhmonov on China's banning of the Falun Gong sect,
Jiang said that China proceeds from safeguarding social stability
in settling the Falun Gong issue.
</P>
<P>
He said that stability is in the best interests of the state
and the people, and nothing can be done without stability, noting
that the decision has won the support of all walks of life and has
been welcomed by the people.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov said that bilateral ties have been developing
steadily, and Tajikistan is satisfied with this. He expressed the
conviction that his talks with President Jiang would help promote
existing friendly and cooperative ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two countries should make full use of their
geographical advantages to further mutually beneficial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two countries share the same or similar views on regional
and international issues, according to the Tajikistan president.
He said that his country opposes big countries or international
blocs trampling on international laws and imposing their will on
others.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China holds that all countries, big or small, are
equal, and said that Tajikistan is prepared to promote
consultations and cooperation with China on international issues.
</P>
<P>
He added that it is important to promote the work of the Sino-
Tajikistan mixed economic and trade commission to push forward
cooperation in this regard.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, he reiterated that Tajikistan takes the
stance that there is only one China, and Taiwan is an inalienable
part of China. 
</P>
