<HEADLINE> Shanghai Customs Cracks Cigarette Smuggling Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Customs of Shanghai, China's
leading industrial and commercial center, today seized more than 4,
000 boxes of suspected contraband cigarettes, valued at 20 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
This afternoon, Customs officials opened five containers
holding imported goods in the Waigaoqiao port area, only to find
that they were full of British-made "555" brand cigarettes, local
sources said.
</P>
<P>
A preliminary investigation indicates that the five containers
belong to a foreign trade company, which claimed that the
containers held other goods than cigarettes on its declaration
form.
</P>
<P>
Such a large case of cigarettes smuggling through general trade
channels is rare in Shanghai, according to Customs officials, and
the case is still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
