<HEADLINE> PLA Condemn Li Hongzhi's Role in Illegal Gathering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- After learning the truth
regarding the illegal gathering at Zhongnanhai by Falun Gong
practitioners on April 25, officers and men of the Chinese People'
s Liberation Army (PLA) and the People's Armed Police Force across
the country noted that the gathering was a well-prepared and well-
organized major political incident.
</P>
<P>
The gathering, which was directly plotted and controlled by Li
Hongzhi, the ringleader of the outlawed Falun Gong cult, was aimed
at exerting pressure on the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
central government, and disrupting the country's stable political
situation, they said.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the illegal gathering at Zhongnanhai,
headquarters of the CPC Central Committee and the central
government, was the most serious political incident since the 1989
political turmoil, and fully unveiled Li's political ambition and
schemes.
</P>
<P>
They said that they fully support the CPC Central Committee's
timely and wise decision to ban Falun Gong in accordance with the
law, and will not tolerate anyone's attempt to destabilize the
country.
</P>
<P>
They pledged to further uncover and criticize the vicious
nature of Li Hongzhi and Falun Gong and to safeguard the country's
stability and unity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
