<HEADLINE> Poll Sees Easy Win for BJP-Led Coalition in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The coalition led by the
Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) will have a comfortable win and
secure between 322 and 336 seats in the coming Lok Sabha (lower
house) elections, an opinion poll by the India Today-Insight
magazine said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The opinion poll was conducted between August 4 and 8 and
covered 20,640 registered voters in 86 constituencies in 16
states.
</P>
<P>
It said that the BJP's vote may touch 32 percent and the party
may enter the new Lok Sabha with nearly 320 MPs.
</P>
<P>
It also predicts between 132 and 146 seats for the Congress
party and its allies and between 70 and 80 for other parties.
</P>
<P>
"Backed by the euphoria of a victorious encounter in Kargil (in
Kashmir) and a series of strategic alliances with powerful
regional players, (BJP leader Atal Bihari) Vajpayee begins the
election campaign with an awesome popularity rating, both
personally and for his government," the magazine said.
</P>
<P>
For the Congress, the magazine said the unresolved confusion
between peddling one-party rule and striking deals with regional
players was proving costly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
