<HEADLINE> Equity Prices in Greece Surge to New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Greek equity prices soared to new
records Friday with the general index on the Athens Stock Exchange
(ASE) ending 2.19 percent higher at 4,799.62 points.
</P>
<P>
This is the third record for the ASE general index within this
week and its 38th record since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ASE general index closed at 4,585.26 points on Tuesday and
the 4,696.91 points on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also ended 1.53 percent up Friday at
2,675.42 points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 219.8 billion drachmas (about 730 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 224 to 65 with another five issues
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
The insurance and holding sectors led the rising stock market
with ending 7.44 and 7.55 percent higher respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
