<HEADLINE> Chinese People Further Perceive True Nature of Falun Gong  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- People across China have said
that they have further penetrated the true nature of Li Hongzhi
and his outlawed Falun Gong sect, after the entire story of the
April 25 illegal gathering at Zhongnanhai by Falun Gong
practitioners was made public Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Some former practitioners at Qinghua University said that they
regretted having been involved in the sect, upon learning of the
behind-the-scenes activities of Li Hongzhi during the gathering.
</P>
<P>
The university staff and students held that the sect was aimed
at disturbing the country's economic development, and jeopardizing
its political situation of stability and unity.
</P>
<P>
People in north China's Tianjin City expressed indignation over
Li and his role in the gathering. The city leadership held
unanimously that the April 25 illegal gathering was a well-planned
incident aimed at exerting pressure upon the Communist Party of
China and the central government, a sign that Li has been
collaborating with anti-China forces both in China and overseas. (
More)
