<HEADLINE> Russian Border Guards to Leave Georgia by November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 13 (Xinhua) -- All Russian troops guarding
Georgia's borders will leave the former Soviet republic by
November 1 this year, Georgian border guard commander Valery
Chkheidze said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The schedule for the pullout was agreed to during talks in
Tbilisi between Chkheidze and Russian deputy border guard chief
Alexander Manilov, Interfax quoted Chkheidze as saying in the
Georgian capital.
</P>
<P>
Chkheidze said he and Manilov had reached a complete, mutual
understanding, "even on such complicated issues as the division of
movable property, including the Russian border guards' weapons."
</P>
<P>
The Russians are leaving half of their weapons to the Georgian
border guards, he said.
</P>
<P>
Manilov told the news conference that nearly all Russian border
guards had already left Georgia.
</P>
<P>
"Only a few dozen officers and their families remain in
Adzharia and Abkhazia. They will be withdrawn to Russia before
November 1," he said, noting that Georgia was providing maximum
assistance in the departure of the Russian guards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
