<HEADLINE> Davids Allowed to Use Diuretic Eye Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Italian Olympic Committee (CONI)
allowed Juventus midfielder Edgar Davids to use eye drops
containing a banned diuretic on Friday.
</P>
<P>
CONI said it had been advised by Rome's anti-doping laboratory
to allow the use of the drops even though they contain the
diuretic dorzolamide.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch midfielder was prescribed the eye drops to treat a
temporary glaucoma which was affecting his vision.
</P>
<P>
Juventus informed CONI on Saturday the affair for dispensation
to use the drug. 
</P>
</TEXT>
