<HEADLINE> Jiang's Visit to Strengthen Sino-Australian Ties: Howard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
upcoming visit to Australia will provide an opportunity to further
strengthen relations between the two countries in the next century,
Australian Prime Minister John Howard said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's visit will be the first one to Australia by a Chinese
president and comes when bilateral relations are enjoying a peak
period.
</P>
<P>
Howard said that Australia and China have established a
cooperative relation that is of great benefit to both countries
and the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
"We share common ground in economic revitalization and reform,
and the improvement of financial management in our region." he
said.
</P>
<P>
Howard said expanding trade and investment exchanges between
China and Australia would bring great gains to both countries and
enhance already-close community links. 
