<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Stresses Progress in Socialist Ethics in Rural Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
stressed that equal importance should be given to increasing
farmers' incomes and keeping stability in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
During an inspection tour of east China's Anhui Province, the
vice-premier said that China's rural reform and development is now
at a crucial stage. While focusing on economic development, local
authorities should also attach great importance to progress in
socialist ethics and democratic and legal construction in rural
areas, in order to maintain stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that enhancing socialist ethical progress is a
significant and long-term task in socialist construction, and its
purpose is to meet the demand of building a new-style rural modern
economy. To achieve this, farmers' ethical, cultural and
scientific qualities should be enhanced, he said.
</P>
<P>
The main task of the rural reform is to enhance farmers'
education in Deng Xiaoping Theory and the guidelines of the
Communist Party, promote scientific and civilized thinking,
strengthen democratic and legal construction and foster the spirit
of hard work, Wen Jiabao noted.
</P>
<P>
Wen said that promotion of socialist ethical progress should be
pursued in line with the development of the local rural economy.
Rural areas at different development levels should be treated
differently, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wen asked local governments to map out plans to promote the
harmonious development of material civilization and ethical
progress, so as to improve the overall economic and social level
in rural China.
</P>
<P>
He also urged local authorities to make more efforts to resolve
farmers' difficulties, so that they might give full play to their
initiative.  
</P>
</TEXT>
