<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PECC China Committee Convenes Ninth Plenary Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The ninth plenary session of the
China National Committee for Pacific Economic Cooperation (PECC)
was held here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
After hearing a report on the current international situation
and a work report of the PECC China National Committee for the
past two years, the session discussed and approved amendments on
the chapters of the national committee as well as a name list of
new committee members.
</P>
<P>
The committee is a non-governmental organization, consisting of
government officials, business people and people in academic
circles.
</P>
<P>
The session agreed that the committee should actively help the
PECC in its work by taking advantage of the committee's wide
connections and high degree of flexibility.
</P>
<P>
The session decided that priority should be given to promoting
China's industrial and commercial enterprises, especially state-
owned large and medium-sized enterprises, to develop in line with
international standards.
</P>
<P>
The PECC, headquarted in Singapore, was established in 1980,
and has 23 member countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
