<HEADLINE> Belarus Sets New World Military Shooting Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Belarus set the new world record
in the women's sports pistol military rapid fire team event in the
shooting competition at the Military World Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
They scored 1,741 points to break the previous record set by
Russia in Switzerland in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The silver medal went to Russia (1,718) here while DPR. Korea (
1,715) edged China to win the bronze.
</P>
<P>
The event is not an Olympic event but is sanctioned by the
International Military Sports Council, which organized the
Military World Games.
</P>
<P>
In the individual competition, Janna Shepelevitch of Belarus
also equaled the world record of 585 points on her way to the top
of the podium.
</P>
<P>
Russia's Marina Logvinenko was second at 584 while Kim Hye Ok
of DPR Korea took home the bronze at 580. 
