<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Kupang, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A tectonic quake measuring 5.7
on the Richter scale jolted Kupang, capital of Indonesia's East
Nusa Tenggara province, and its environs at 10:56 a.m. local time
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The quake's epicenter was traced at the Timor Sea, about 49
kilometers southeast of Kupang and 33 kilometers beneath the sea
level, head of the local meteorological and geophysical office
Fransisca Surti Priyani told the Antara News Agency.
</P>
<P>
No casualty or damage has been reported.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Thursday, a quake measuring 6.0 on the Richter scale
rocked Luwuk city in Central Sulawesi. 
