<HEADLINE> Rainstorm Hits Central China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A rainstorm battered Chenzhou
City in central China's Hunan Province from 8:00 am Thursday to 8:
00 am today, with precipitation reaching 295 mm, or one third of
the annual average.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, four sq km of urban areas, eight
bridges, 100 ha of cropland and 200 ha of vegetable fields were
inundated.
</P>
<P>
Initial figures show that more than 120,000 people were
affected, with 100,000 dwellings, 1,000 factories and 200 schools
and government office buildings flooded.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 inhabitants of a suburban village have been
stranded on the roofs of their houses by flooding, and the local
government has sent a police team to rescue them.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the rainfall, the water level in two reservoirs
in the Beihu district of the city has almost reached the top of
the dams, with a possible danger of over-spilling.
</P>
<P>
The Hunan provincial government has sent three battalions of
militia, reserve forces and armed police to Chenzhou. 
</P>
</TEXT>
