<HEADLINE> Tibet's State-Owned Enterprises Reduce Losses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Tibet's 30 key State-owned
enterprises reduced losses by 43.93 million yuan (about 5.29
million U.S. dollars) in the first six months of this year thanks
to a series of reform policies.
</P>
<P>
Financial revenue for the regional government increased by 70
percent during the period compared with the same 1998 period, with
60 percent of this revenue coming from State-owned enterprises.
</P>
