said, "we reiterate our support for the relevant resolutions on
Angola adopted by the SADC summit held in Mauritius last year and
by the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
"We should work to turn southern Africa into a region of peace,
 stability and unity," said the Mozambican premier.
</P>
<P>
The two-day ministerial session which opened here Friday will
make preparations for the SADC summit scheduled here next
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi said the SADC summit has provided an opportunity for
the 14 member states to think over the organization's past, sum up
the present and work out plans for the future.
</P>
