and Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma also made speeches at the opening
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
As chair lady of the ministerial meeting ot the SADC, Zuma
stressed that at the meeting, the southern African countries
should sum up the history to end conflicts and work for the
sustainable development of economy and society in the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministers of the 14 SADC countries and representatives
of regional organizations were present at the ceremony held at
Rovuma Hotel in Maputo Friday morning. 
