<HEADLINE> Agency Chief Believed to Be Target of Bombing in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Lawmen investigating the
explosion at the Philippines' National Bureau of Investigation
(NBI) overnight said Friday that the agency's chief of the Special
Investigation Division (SID) could be the target of the bombing.
</P>
<P>
The explosion killed seven men, six of them NBI agents, and
wounded 12 people. Those wounded were brought to different
hospitals in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
NBI Director Federico Opinion said the explosion took place at
the SID office at the ground floor of the NBI headquarters in Taft
avenue, Manila, shortly after midnight Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It left heavy damage to the SID office, sparking a fire which
affected the Security Management Division and the Quality Control
Department of the NBI, both at the ground floor of the building.
</P>
<P>
The Western Police District Bomb Disposal Unit and Arson Group
were helping the NBI in the probe of the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Opinion said they were looking into the possibility that the
target of those behind the explosion could be the SID chief,
lawyer Ruel Lazala.
</P>
<P>
Lazala headed a team which conducted a big drug operation
recently, the NBI chief said. The SID office was charged with
investigation in big time drug syndicates, gunrunning groups and
other notorious criminals.
</P>
<P>
Other reports said the explosion occurred just after the SID
came from a raid in Paranaque city, where some Muslim suspects
were brought to the office.
</P>
<P>
Several firearms and ammunition as well as office equipment and
documents were reportedly damaged by the explosion.
</P>
<P>
An inventory of losses as a result of the explosion was still
being conducted by the NBI.
</P>
<P>
Another angle being pursued in the probe of the incident was
the possibility of terrorist hand in the bombing.
</P>
<P>
At the height of the clearing operations at the SID office, the
NBI was reported to have received another bomb threat, one of the
several they have received in the past days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
