<HEADLINE> China and Tajikistan Sign Joint Statement (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The People's Republic of China
and the Republic of Tajikistan signed a joint statement here today
on promoting bilateral good-neighborly, friendly, and mutually
beneficial cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Tajikistan's President
Emomali Rakhmonov signed the document on behalf of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
It says that, during the high-level talks and meetings during
Rakhmonov's goodwill visit, the two sides discussed promoting
cooperation in all fields and regional and global issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
It says that promoting bilateral good-neighborly, friendly and
cooperative ties is in the fundamental interest of the two
countries and that progress in solving border issues left over by
history is significant. The two will adhere to the contents of the
joint Sino-Tajik statement on basic principles for mutual
relations of March 9, 1993 and the joint statement of September 16,
1996.
</P>
<P>
The two are satisfied with the growth of mutually beneficial
cooperation in politics, economy, culture, science, technology,
and education since they established diplomatic ties and have the
determination to stick to the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence and maintain and develop long-term, stable, good-
neighborly, friendly, and mutually beneficial cooperative ties.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China and Tajikistan Sign Joint Statement (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The two highly value the border agreement signed by the two
heads of state during Rakhmonov's China visit, it says, and, on
the basis of this and in accordance with acknowledged
international practices, the two agree to continue negotiations on
the borderline that have not been settled, in the spirit of equal
consultations and mutual accommodations for an early and
successful solution.
</P>
<P>
The agreement says the two sides agree to maintain the current
situation along the border until a final solution is found.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will also make use of geographical advantages and
increase cooperation in economy and trade and further this
cooperation at the national level and the provincial level and
along the border areas, and direct contacts between firms and
enterprises of China and Tajikistan will be encouraged and
supported. The governments of the two countries will create more
favorable conditions for such cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The function of inter-governmental economic and trade
committees will be expanded, it says, and bilateral economic and
trade agreements already in place should be implemented and
problems that occur in relation to this should be tackled promptly.
</P>
</TEXT>
