<HEADLINE> Many Chinese Cities Polluted by Suspended Particles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The large amount of suspended
particles was the major reason for air pollution in many Chinese
cities this week, according to the latest weekly air-quality
report released by the China Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
From August 6 to 13, the cities of Nanning, Qinhuangdao,
Lianyungang, Wenzhou, Fuzhou, Guilin, Dalian, Zhuhai, Qinghai,
Zhanjiang, Xiamen, Haikou, and Beihai all enjoyed excellent air
quality, and the air quality of 28 cities including Guangzhou, Xi'
an, Chongqing, and Beijing was good.
</P>
<P>
The air quality of Hohhot, Urumqi, Shanghai, and Taiyuan was
slightly polluted during the period, while Lanzhou reported
moderate air pollution.
</P>
<P>
Lanzhou and 17 other cities had their air affected by suspended
particles. Sulfur dioxide was the major problem in Chongqing,
while Shanghai, Guangzhou, and Shenzhen had nitrogen oxide in the
air as their major problem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
