<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Postal Service Achieves Rapid Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China's postal service has made
a great leap forward in network size, technological level, and
service quality, displaying a sustainable, speedy, and sound
development over the past 50 years, according to the State Postal
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, there were 84,134 post offices in
China, with postal routes running to 2.85 million kilometers,
forming a comprehensive and efficient postal transportation
network.
</P>
<P>
Since the founding of New China in 1949, the country has
adhered to the principle of "developing the post through science
and technology," and has introduced advanced equipment and
technology from overseas.
</P>
<P>
Thus far, China has 16,272 computerized post offices, 106
automatic letter sorters, and 138 automatic parcel sorters, and
the creation of a comprehensive postal computer network is now
underway.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with market demands, China Posts has
progressively established several professional institutions, such
as the China Courier Service Company, the China Post Advertising
Company, and the China Post Mail Order Company.
</P>
<P>
Four categories of services are now provided: postal delivery,
newspaper and magazine distribution, philately, and postal savings
and remittance services.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Postal Service Achieves Rapid Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New service items such as data posts and merchandise mail
ordering are now also provided.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the revenue from postal services amounted to 28.7
billion yuan, noted the SPB.
</P>
<P>
With the acceleration of facilities construction, China Posts
has also improved its services. At the same time, China Posts has
pledged to solve several urgent problems related to the public
interest. With these efforts, phenomenon such as impolite service
attitudes on the part of employees has been basically eliminated.
</P>
<P>
In the past 50 years, China Posts has also established wide-
ranging cooperation with other countries. By the end of last year,
the country has set up direct postal services with 145 countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
International correspondences and parcels are now able to reach
every corner of the world, and express mail services now reach
some 200 countries and regions. 
</P>
