<HEADLINE> Pakistani People Sharing Joy of Founding of New China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- As a close friend of China, the
Pakistani people would like to share the joy of the Chinese people
who will celebrate the 50th anniversary of the founding of the
People's Republic of China on October 1.
</P>
<P>
Iftikhar Hussain Kazmi, interim charge d'affaires of the
Pakistani Embassy, made the remarks in an interview with Xinhua
prior to the 52nd anniversary of Pakistan's Independence Day,
which falls on August 14.
</P>
<P>
Kazmi said, Pakistan will hold a series of events from
September 18 to 25, including a seminar on China in the 21st
century and painting and photo exhibits highlighting China's
progress in the past decades.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Chinese artists will be invited to perform Chinese
dances, music and acrobatics in several Pakistani cities, and a
Chinese film festival will also be held.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani people are equally happy and rejoicing at the
founding of the People's Republic of China, Kazmi said, adding
that increased people-to-people contacts will promote mutual
understanding, and will also be helpful to the growth of
friendship and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Describing Sino-Pakistani relations as "close, cordial and
cooperative," the Pakistani diplomat said that this friendship is
a model for countries with different social systems, what leaders
of the two countries have called "time-tested and all-weather
friendship."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0199 </DOCNO>
