<HEADLINE> Pakistani People Sharing Joy of Founding of New China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He also noted that bilateral economic and trade ties are not
strong as political relations, and said that potential in these
areas need to be tapped.
</P>
<P>
During the visit to China last June by Pakistan's Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif, an agreement was signed on setting up a
business council to promote trade links between the two countries.
"That will give some push to Sino-Pakistani economic and trade
relations," said Kazmi.
</P>
<P>
Noting that many Chinese companies are doing good business in
Pakistan in telecommunications, energy, oil, land, infrastructure,
and other areas, he said he believes that much remains to be done
to further bilateral cooperation in this regard.
</P>
