<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Rejects Nicaragua Proposal on Taiwan's Status (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao today expressed strong condemnation of and
firm opposition to a proposal by Nicaragua and a number of other
countries calling for discussions of Taiwan's "representation" in
the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that Nicaragua and several other countries recently
sent a letter to the U.N. Secretary-General asking for a
discussion of Taiwan's "representation" in the U.N., which is an
open attempt to create "two Chinas" or "one China, one Taiwan."
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out: "This is a wilful trample on the purpose and
principles of the U.N. Charter and gross interference in China's
internal affairs, and we strongly condemn and firmly oppose this."
</P>
<P>
The United Nations is an intergovernmental international
organization composed of sovereign states, and its member
countries can only be sovereign states, he said.
</P>
<P>
There is only one China in the world, and the government of the
People's Republic of China is the sole legal representative of the
entire Chinese people, and Taiwan is a part of China, Zhu said,
adding that this is an internationally recognized fact and
therefore Taiwan has no qualifications whatsoever for joining the
U.N. and its special agencies in any form.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0202 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Rejects Nicaragua Proposal on Taiwan's Status (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The spokesman also said that the representation of the People's
Republic of China in the United Nations was solved in a just,
thorough and complete way according to the Resolution N0. 2758
which was adopted by an overwhelming majority during the 26th U.N.
General Assembly 28 years ago.
</P>
<P>
This resolution, which conformed to historical trends, clearly
declares that the representative of the Government of the People's
Republic of China is the sole legal representative of China in the
U.N. organization, and also decided to restore all the rights of
the People's Republic of China in the United Nations and
immediately expelled the representatives of the Taiwan authorities
from the posts Taiwan authorities had illegally occupied in the
United Nations and all the UN agencies, he said.
</P>
<P>
The resolution not only has safeguarded the purpose and
principles of the U.N. Charter, but also defeated the conspiracy
of a small number of countries to attempt to create "two Chinas"
in the U.N. that year, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, Zhu said, the General Committee of the U.N. General
Assembly every year has clearly refused to put the so-called "
representation issue" of Taiwan on their agenda, and this fully
demonstrates the firm stand of the majority member states of the U.
N. in safeguarding the authoritativeness of the U.N. Charter and
the Resolution 2758, Zhu said, adding that it also shows that any
conspiracy and attempt that go against the will of the majority of
U.N. member states are futile and very unpopular.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan authorities are going against historical trend, and
while asserting the "two-state" remark, they instigate a small
number of countries to raise the issue of Taiwan's "representation
" in the United Nations, and this further reveals their stubborn
stand of sticking to split China, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
 Nevertheless, he added, no matter what intrigues the Taiwan
authorities resort to or what pretext they cook up for "joining"
the United Nations, they will not be able to change the ending
that they are doomed to failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
