sending troop reinforcements to the field as the conflict is
taking on a scale of open war threatening the small Caucasus
republic.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- After designating Vladimir Putin as his candidate for the
2000 presidential election and naming him as prime minister,
Russian President Boris Yeltsin is launching a ``massive''
offensive against the Islamic rebels who are engaged in a ``holy
war'' against Russia in the Caucasus.
</P>
<P>
-- The chief of Kosovo Albanians, Ibrahim Rugova, who returned
to Pristina early this month after two and a half months of exile
in Italy, declared to the French press on Thursday that he is
ready to join the Transitional Council of Kosovo, the consultative
organ established by the U.N. which he has boycotted until now.
</P>
</TEXT>
