<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Recapture Bagram Airbase: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Afghanistan's ruling Taliban
militia Friday recaptured the Bagram airbase, 50 kilometers north
of Kabul, the Afghan Islamic Press (AIP) reported.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistan-based news agency said forces loyal to former
defense minister Ahmad Shah Masood retreated from the base after
Taliban troops entered without a fight.
</P>
<P>
No independent sources have so far confirmed the news.
</P>
<P>
Bagram had been the only airbase of the Masood forces. They and
the Taliban militia have repeatedly changed hands on the airbase
during the large-scale fighting since late July.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban Thursday said the airbase was under the control of
neither side, but the opposition claimed to having been holding
it.
</P>
<P>
"As of this morning, the airbase was still held by the
opposition," said opposition spokesman Abdullah on Friday.
</P>
