<HEADLINE> Foreign Residents in S. Tome to Vote in Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Some of Sao Tome and Principle's
foreign residents from other member countries of the Community of
Portuguese- speaking Countries (CPLP) will have a right to vote in
some elections to be held in the archipelago country.
</P>
<P>
A decree approved by the Parliament of Sao Tome and Principles
Thursday permits those foreign residents who have been living in
Sao Tome since the independence of the country in July of 1975 to
be registered as voters.
</P>
<P>
The decree, which obtained support by the ruling party Social
Democratic Party, also called Liberation Movement of Sao Tome and
Principles, was approved by a margin of eight, with 30 votes for,
22 against and one abstention.
</P>
<P>
According to the newly-approved decree, the qualified foreign
residents can enjoy equal rights as the Sao Tome citizens, except
exercise of the right of voting in autarkical elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
