<HEADLINE> New Arterial Roads Completed in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines has completed a
total of 282 kilometers of arterial roads in southern Mindanao,
said an official of the Department of Public Works and Highways
(DPWH) Region XI on Friday.
</P>
<P>
DPWH Region XI Director Juanito Abergas said a total of 440
million pesos (11 million U.S. dollars) worth of completed roads
and bridges upped the level of productivity in Region XI, making
investments 6.5 percent higher than in the previous years.
</P>
<P>
Abergas said the DPWH's accomplishments were made even more
significant as the projects were completed despite difficulties
brought about by the Asia financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
He said funding for the projects came from various sources,
including the Regular Infrastructure Program, Additional Priority
Projects Fund, School Building Program, the Countryside
Development Fund, and General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade
Program.
</P>
<P>
Also completed are four bridges under the Japan's Bridge Grant
Aid. Three other bridges are still under on-going status. 
</P>
</TEXT>
