<HEADLINE> Chinese Expedition Ship Anchors Near Canadian Port </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SNOW DRAGON SHIP, August 13 (Xinhua)-- The first Chinese Arctic
expedition team arrived near the Canadian port of Tuktoyaktuk this
morning.
</P>
<P>
After completing the first phase of its oceanic, atmospheric,
and ice research in the Arctic Ocean, the expedition ship Snow
Dragon is at anchor 15 nautical miles outside the Tuktoyaktuk port
after a 40 hour voyage.
</P>
<P>
The expedition members will meet with another team composed of
60 overseas Chinese scientists, who will visit the ship and take
part in academic exchanges. This activity has been organized by
the Canadian Outdoor Recreation and Conservation Association (
CORCA).
</P>
<P>
Some members of the expedition will be invited to the Canadian
city of Inuvik to attend a reception sponsored by the city
government.
</P>
<P>
The Snow Dragon will leave for a return voyage to the Arctic
Ocean this weekend to launch the final phase of its scientific
research.  
</P>
</TEXT>
