<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Some 700 Million Tons of Garbage Besiege Beijing Residents: Investigation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua)-- The Chinese capital is
overburdened by enormous amounts of solid waste, and
environmentalists have urged the drafting of laws and policies to
speed up garbage disposal, according to a report in the Beijing
Economic Daily.
</P>
<P>
A research team organized by the Beijing Municipal Committee of
the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang (RCCK), one
of China's democratic parties, recently conducted an investigation
on garbage disposal in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The investigation found the garbage generated by Beijing
enterprises and residents amounts to a total of 600 million to 700
million tons, "which means each urban dweller is besieged by 100
tons of garbage," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The research team has called for legislation to speed up and
regulate disposal work, and garbage disposal fees may be charged
on enterprises and residents.
</P>
<P>
They also urged the municipal government to publish
preferential policies to encourage factories to recycle their
rubbish.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Environmental and Sanitation Management
Bureau plans to build four refuse-burning power stations near
Beijing, which will consume 4,200 tons of garbage daily.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's investment in the construction of environmental
protection infrastructure between 1996 and 2000 will reach 1.1
billion yuan (133 million U.S. dollars), and 100 percent of the
daily rubbish will be processed by the year 2010, the bureau said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
