<HEADLINE> Egypt Urges India, Pakistan to Exercise Restraint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Egypt has urged India and Pakistan
to exercise restraint over their latest military confrontation,
Al-Akhbar daily reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
An Egyptian Foreign Ministry spokesman said on Thursday that
Egypt hopes that India and Pakistan will have calm relations so
that they can resolve their existing disputes.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, speaking on customary condition of anonymity,
called on the two South Asian nuclear-armed rivals to avoid
further escalation of the tensions and seek peaceful solution to
their disputes.
</P>
<P>
Tensions soared between Islamabad and New Delhi after Indian
fighter jets shot down a Pakistani military aircraft on Tuesday,
killing all 16 crew members. After the attack, the troops along
the border of the countries were on high alert.
</P>
<P>
India accused the Pakistani plane of crossing into its air
space while Pakistan said the aircraft was inside its own air
space when it was attacked.
</P>
<P>
India and Pakistan fought three wars during the last 50 years
over their disputes in Kashmir, an area both countries have
claimed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
