<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taxi Drivers in Hong Kong Gear up for Courtesy Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Tourist
Association (HKTA) Friday launched a program to promote the
message of courtesy among taxi drivers.
</P>
<P>
The move is a highlight of the HKTA's community-wide "Be A Good
Host" campaign, said a spokesman for the HKTA at a press
conference.
</P>
<P>
The program aims to raise drivers' awareness of the importance
of the tourism industry to Hong Kong and of the vital work they
can do to make overseas guests feel welcome, as drivers are
recognized as being among the most prominent of front-line service
staff in promoting the city, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
"Through the program, they will be encouraged to provide
courteous and high-quality service, delivered in a sincere manner,
" the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey jointly conducted by the HKTA and Lingnan
University shows that of the qualities of a courteous taxi driver,
the top four responses were "friendliness", "good driving skills",
"a ready smile" and "good language proficiency."
</P>
<P>
More than 500 people were interviewed during the survey,
through which the HKTA aims to help taxi drivers better understand
expectations of passengers and that they can become "good host" by
improving their overall service standards, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The HKTA and Radio Television Hong Kong will also organize a
series of taxi driver-related activities in the coming two months,
including special radio program carrying the theme "courteous taxi
drivers and taxi association operators." 
</P>
</TEXT>
