<HEADLINE> 7 Confirmed Dead in Explosion in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Seven fatalities have been
confirmed in the powerful explosion that ripped through the
Philippine National Bureau of Investigation (NBI) in Manila early
Friday.
</P>
<P>
An initial police report said the seven dead include six NBI
agents -- one supervising agent, two special investigators and
three confidential agents. The death report also involved a
lawyer.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said the explosion killed eight persons and
injured 12. Still, no report has been released on the number of
the people in the building when the accident occurred.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency (PNA) said NBI Director Opinion has
formed a probe team to investigate the explosion and death of some
of his NBI men.
</P>
<P>
A few hours after the explosion and fire, an unidentified man
called up by telephone the NBI office and threatened to blow up
the main NBI building, the PNA quoted Opinion as saying.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, NBI employees were ordered to vacate the building,
while a search operation to clear it of any bomb was being
conducted.
</P>
<P>
However, the bomb threat proved to be false and the NBI workers
returned to their offices, Opinion said.
</P>
<P>
Opinion said the NBI did not know yet the cause of the
explosion as this was being probed yet.
</P>
<P>
But he said the explosion occurred just after the NBI's special
investigation division (SID) came from a raid in Paranaque City,
where some Muslim suspects were brought to the office.
</P>
<P>
According to Opinion, the SID office was one of the
high-profile NBI offices charged with investigations on big time
drug syndicates, gunrunning groups and other notorious criminals.
</P>
</TEXT>
