<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Holds Legal Affairs Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The legal panel of the
Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative Region
(SAR) held its 16th session in Beijing on August 10-12.
</P>
<P>
According to a news release today, the meeting focused on
contradictions between the original laws of Macao and the Macao
SAR Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The extensive consensus reached at these discussions is
expected to lay the foundation for proposals in this regard by the
Macao SAR Preparatory Committee to be submitted to the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
The meeting also discussed other national legal affairs and
suggested that two national laws be added to Appendix III of the
Macao SAR Basic Law: national laws to be applied in the Macao
Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
The two laws are the Law of the People's Republic of China on
the Exclusive Economic Zone and the Continental Shelf and The Law
on Stationing Troops in the Macao Special Administrative Region (
SAR).  
</P>
