<DOCNO> XIE19990813.0239 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 08:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Polygamy Impairs Stability in UAE Families </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Polygamy and marriages
involving different nationalities pose the greatest threat to the
stability of families in the United Arab Emirates (UAE), according
to a recent poll.
2 4@5
</P>
<P>
Some 72 percent of the men and 70 percent of the women
investigated agree that polygamy is one of the main destabilizing
factors of UAE families, says the poll published in the August
issue of Al Mawadda, an Abu Dhabi-based quarterly magazine.
</P>
<P>
In a Muslim country like the UAE, men are allowed to have up to
four wives. Wives are confined to their houses for most of the
time.
</P>
<P>
The poll, in the form of answering a questionnaire, was
attended by 50 men and 50 women. All the women and half of the men
believe that the difference in nationalities of husband and wife
is also a primary negative factor of family instability.
</P>
<P>
Marriages between UAE men and foreign women have been
increasing in recent years. However, at least 60 percent of such
marriages end in divorce due to difference in cultural backgrounds.
</P>
<P>
In some Gulf countries, marrying foreign women are not
allowed. The UAE may also take the measure someday, sociologists
say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
