<HEADLINE> Chinese Police Round Up 50,000 Fugitives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese police, in the latest
campaign against escaped prisoners, have so far captured some 50,
000 fugitives including criminal suspects and convicts.
</P>
<P>
The nationwide campaign was begun on July 1 by the Ministry of
Public Security to eliminate possible troubles and create a better
environment for the celebration of the 50th founding anniversary
of the People's Republic of China, and celebrations for the return
of Macao to the motherland, said a high-ranking police officer.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry established an information network to provide
police unites nationwide with detailed information on the
fugitives in an effort to improve the campaign's effectiveness,
the official said, adding that more than 30,000 criminal suspects
already captured were in the network's files.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, in order to mobilize the masses of people to fight
against criminals, the ministry plans to offer rewards to citizens
who provide tips or help round up the escapees. "The new measure
will help improve the fighting capability of the campaign," the
officer said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
