<HEADLINE> Ho Chi Minh City's Export Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Ho Chi Minh City grossed an export
turnover of 2.47 billion U.S. dollars in the first seven months of
this year, 14.5 percent more than the corresponding period last
year, Vietnam News Agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's biggest economic hub's high value increases were
recorded in the export of sea products (9 percent), crude oil (25
percent), industrial products (20.5 percent), and rubber (10.8
percent).
</P>
<P>
Foreign-invested enterprises in the city earned 515 million
U.S. dollars from exports, a year-on-year increase of 37.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
In the reviewed period, the city's exports to the Republic of
Korea, Singapore, Indonesia, France and Germany increased while
its exports to Japan, the Philippines, Malaysia, Thailand and
Russia saw remarkable decreases. 
</P>
