<HEADLINE> Large Farm Machinery Plant Operational in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Yanmar Agricultural
Equipment (China) Co., Ltd., a Sino-Japanese joint venture,
recently became operational in the city of Wuxi in east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The venture is jointly funded by the Jiangsu Farm Machinery and
Petroleum Company, the Wuxi New Area Development Group, Japan's
Yanmar Agricultural Equipment Co., Ltd., and Seirei Industry Co.,
Ltd., with initial investment of 29.98 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The new company will mainly manufacture rice and wheat combines
specially designed for the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The plant is scheduled to turn out 3,000 combines next year,
and its annual production capacity will eventually reach 20,000
annually.
</P>
<P>
The company has already set up more than 30 service centers
across China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
