<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coal Mine Explosion Kills Seven </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 13 (Xinhua)-- A major coal mine explosion in
east China's Zhejiang Province killed seven people and slightly
injured one person yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at the Changguang Coal Mine in northern
Zhejiang, bordering Anhui Province, at 4:30 on Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Provincial Vice-Governor Ye Rongbao rushed to the site at the
head of a group of local officials, who are in charge of
provincial coal industry, labor, public security and supervision
bureaus and provincial trade union organization, to direct rescue
work shortly after the explosion.
</P>
<P>
On December 29 last year, 32 people were killed and more than
10 injured in another mine explosion when coal miners violated
safety regulations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
