<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Third Generation Of Lion Cubs At Shanghai Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to Shanghai's Xinmin Evening News, the lioness was
discovered to be ready to give birth by zookeepers a month ago and
was given a great deal of care. She gave birth to the four cubs at
the end of July but abandoned them and refused to take care of
them.
</P>
<P>
So, the zookeepers adopted the four, feeding them milk powder
for dogs five times a day, and keeping them in boxes at a steady
temperature of 28 degrees centigrade. They are now doing quite
well thanks to the care of the zookeepers.
</P>
<P>
In April, five other cubs in the northern city of Shijiazhuang
were wet-nursed by a dog because the mother lion had insufficient
milk. 
</P>
</TEXT>
