<HEADLINE> China to Hold Annual Meeting on Multilateral Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- A 4th annual Chinese meeting on
multilateral economic and technology cooperation in developing
countries is scheduled to be held in September in the city of
Yinchuan in Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is held under the auspices of the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), which has helped multilateral
cooperation programs in more than 100 countries around the world.
The UNDP's China connection, China network, has 17 members in
Beijing, Guangzhou, Lanzhou, Chengdu and other major cities.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was organized by China's International Economic
Exchange Center and the Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region's Science
and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
Yinchuan also wants to use this opportunity to inform UNDP
officials and China network members of its latest development in
hope of getting more assistance.
</P>
<P>
China has had UNDP help in many big multilateral projects like
a methane application training center, freshwater fish breeding
center, and the New Eurasian Continental Bridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
