<HEADLINE> First SOS Children's Village Completed in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Construction of 15 houses at
Social Society (SOS) Children's Village has been completed in
Zambian capital Lusaka and is ready to accommodate the first
intake of street children soon.
</P>
<P>
SOS Children's Village of Zambia Trust Project director
Robinson Kayola said all the necessary equipment required for the
first intake of the street children was installed.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by Friday's The Post newspaper as saying: "we are
winding up the installation of equipment as part of our
preparation to receive the first children next month."
</P>
<P>
He said Thursday that only children with no one to look after
them would be considered at the village.
</P>
<P>
According to Kayola, the village would accommodate children
aged below 12.
</P>
<P>
A check at the site found the houses equipped with among other
things refrigerators, stoves, lounge seats and musical sets.
</P>
<P>
Kayola said all the 29 women who were in May selected to
undertake the duties of village mothers were sent to Zimbabwe for
eight weeks skills training in keeping and reforming children in
distress.
</P>
<P>
Mothers' representative Susan Mwandila said her colleagues were
set to receive the first intake of children.
</P>
<P>
"With the skills we attained in Zimbabwe, my team is looking
forward to achieving our objective of creating a sense of
belonging among the children, " said Mwandila.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the project was funded by SOS Kindrdorf
International. 
</P>
</TEXT>
