<HEADLINE> Chinese Folk Art Festival Set for October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, August 13 (Xinhua)-- The 4th China Folk Art Festival
is scheduled to be held on October 8-11 in the city of Wuxi in
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Mongolians, Manchurians, Tibetans, Uygurs, and members of 19
other Chinese ethnic groups will put on show their unique songs
and dances, and exhibit their handicrafts and customs at the city.
</P>
<P>
The festival is sponsored by the China Federation of Literary
and Art Circles, the China Folk Artists Association, and the local
government.
</P>
<P>
Wuxi has the world's tallest bronze Buddha, an 88-meter tall
statue, and other tourist resources. 
