<HEADLINE> Kenya Halts Importing Computers With Millenium Bug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government has issued
a legal notice prohibiting importation of computers, data bases
and other processing equipment without Y2K compliance, Kenya
Times reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The action was intended to prevent from the dumping of cheap
but obsolete technology and equipment from developed countries,
according to Kenyan Finance Minister Francis Masakhalia.
</P>
<P>
The private sector can take the opportunity to update their
information technology so as to keep the east African country's
technology at par with the rest of the world, Masakhalia said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, Kenya formed a committee on Y2K issues to
coordinate the efforts between various sectors of the economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
