<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Chinese Industrial Province Reports Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Exports from China's Liaoning
Province, a major industrial center, were worth 3.21 billion U.S.
dollars in the first half of the year, up 5 percent on a year-on-
year basis.
</P>
<P>
This comes as good news in view of the negative impact of the
Asian financial crisis, says one provincial foreign trade official,
who explained that Liaoning's exports lost about a third over the
past two years as a result of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
To offset the impact, the province has tried to explore new
markets in Western Europe and North America, while maintaining
cooperation with Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
In the January-June period of this year, exports from overseas-
funded enterprises in Liaoning grew 13.6 percent to 1.76 billion U.
S. dollars and machinery and electrical appliance exports were up
15.6 percent to 1.27 billion U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
