<HEADLINE> Davenport Rolls into Acura Classic Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Lindsay Davenport of the
United States cruised to a 6-2, 6-2 victory over Germany's Anke
Huber today to advance to the quarter-finals at the $520,000 Acura
Classic tennis event in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
The top seed and defending champion is taking out her
frustration over losing the No. 1 ranking.
</P>
<P>
Seventh seed Barbara Schett of Austria also advanced when
Natasha Zvereva of Belarus retired in the second set with a
sprained right ankle. Schett lost the first set 6-2, and was
leading the second 4-2.
</P>
<P>
Schett will face second seed and new world No. 1 Martina Hingis
of Switzerland in Friday's quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Davenport's next round opponent will be Conchita Martinez of
Spain, who beat Corina Morariu 7-5, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded American teenager Serena Williams became the first
player to secure a semi-final berth with a 6-2, 6-3 win tonight
over fourth seed Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario of Spain.
</P>
<P>
Less than a week ago, Davenport had to fight off Huber 7-5, 7-5
in the quarter-finals of the TIG Tennis Classic in San Diego. But
it was a different story today as Davenport stormed to victory in
50 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Davenport improved to 19-2 in her last 21 matches in California,
with both of those defeats coming at the hands of sisters Venus
and Serena Williams.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Mary Pierce of France will face countrywoman Julie
Halard-Decugis on Friday after both won their second-round matches
on Wednesday. 
</P>
