<HEADLINE> Lamar Odom Signs with NBA Clippers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 12 (Xinhua) -- Multi-talented forward Lamar
Odom, the latest youngster tabbed as savior for the woeful Los
Angeles Clippers, today signed a three-year deal with the team
worth nearly $8.9 million.
</P>
<P>
Many believed Odom would be the first overall pick in the draft,
but a series of inexplicable moves seriously hurt his status. He
failed to show up for his physical examination and tried to re-
enter Rhode Island after hiring and firing an agent.
</P>
<P>
Under the collective bargaining agreement, Odom could receive a
three-year deal worth a maximum of $8.861 million, plus a club
option for a fourth year for more than $3.86 million.
</P>
<P>
Odom declared for the NBA draft on the last possible day,
forgoing his final two years of eligibility. He is a rare talent,
a player with size who can play on the wing. His dribbling skills
are exceptional.
</P>
<P>
Odom shot 48.2 percent from the field but only 33 percent from
3-point range and committed nearly as many turnover as assists.
</P>
<P>
With abilities that fit four positions, Odom played only one
season at Rhode Island but turned into the team's star, averaging
17.4 points, 9.4 rebounds and 3.8 assists as he led the Rams to
the NCAA Tournament. His regular season totlas helped him garner
first team All-Atlantic 10 Conference honors and Atlantic 10
Rookie of the Year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
