<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Industrial Output Up 5.6 Percent in Q1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 13 (Xinhua) -- Indian industrial output as
measured by the index of Industrial Production (IIP) registered a
modest growth of 5.6 percent in the first quarter (April-June) of
the current fiscal year as against 4.5 percent recorded a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
According to the quick estimates of IIP released by the Central
Statistical Organization (CSO), the moderate resurgence in growth
was led by the manufacturing sector which recorded a growth of 6.5
percent in April-June 1999 against 4.2 percent in April-June 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, growth in the electricity sector was lower at 4.1
percent against 10.2 percent and mining output registered a
negative 0.6 percent growth.
</P>
<P>
On a monthly basis, the growth in industrial output was
estimated at 5.5 percent in June as against 4.8 percent in the
same month of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
