<HEADLINE> New Container Service Route to Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, August 13 (Xinhua) -- China International Ocean
Shipping Containers Co. Ltd inaugurated its second container
service route to Europe at Haicang in this port city in east China
's Fujian Province Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The company, one of the country's two major container shipping
companies, will use ten cargo liners with a total capacity of 2,
000 TEUs of containers to serve the new route.
</P>
<P>
The company's container ships will make port calls at Dalian,
Ningbo, Xiamen, Hong Kong, Chi Wan, Jakarta, Felixstowe, Rotterdam,
Hamburg and Antwerp. The ships will also make port calls at
Singapore on their return voyages.
</P>
<P>
The company's first such route was inaugurated on April 25 this
year. Ships on this first route make port calls at Tianjin,
Qingdao, Shanghai, Hong Kong, Singapore, Rotterdam, Hamburg and
Felixstowe. 
