<HEADLINE> Foreigners Learning More About China Through Language Studies (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Last week, China gave awards to 85 teachers who studied from
1961 to 1964 for their teaching efforts. Vice-minister of
Education Wei Yu said that the teachers had been to some 50
countries and had contributed a great deal in teaching Chinese to
foreigners over the past three decades.
</P>
<P>
China now has over 5,000 people trained to teach Chinese to
foreigners and about 350 universities with foreign students, which
had more than 43,000 foreigners last year, 85 percent of them
studying Chinese language and culture.
</P>
